t: Psalm 9
To the chief Musician upon Muthlabben, A Psalm of David.
I*p will praise thee, O Lord,*s with my whole heart; I will shew forth all thy marvellous works.
I*p will be glad and rejoice in thee: I will sing praise to thy name, O thou most High.
When*p mine enemies are turned back, they shall fall and perish at thy presence.
For*p thou hast maintained my right and my cause; thou satest in the throne judging right.
Thou*p hast rebuked the heathen, thou hast destroyed the wicked, thou hast put out their name for ever and ever.
O*p thou enemy, destructions are come to a perpetual end: and thou hast destroyed cities; their memorial is perished with them.
But*p the Lord*s shall endure for ever: he hath prepared his throne for judgment.
And*p he shall judge the world in righteousness, he shall minister judgment to the people in uprightness.
The*p Lord*s also will be a refuge for the oppressed, a refuge in times of trouble.
And*p they that know thy name will put their trust in thee: for thou, Lord,*s hast not forsaken them that seek thee.
Sing*p praises to the Lord,*s which dwelleth in Zion: declare among the people his doings.
When*p he maketh inquisition for blood, he remembereth them: he forgetteth not the cry of the humble.
Have*p mercy upon me, O Lord;*s consider my trouble which I suffer of them that hate me, thou that liftest me up from the gates of death:
That*p I may shew forth all thy praise in the gates of the daughter of Zion: I will rejoice in thy salvation.
The*p heathen are sunk down in the pit that they made: in the net which they hid is their own foot taken.
The*p Lord*s is known by the judgment which he executeth: the wicked is snared in the work of his own hands. Higgaion. Selah.
The*p wicked shall be turned into hell, and all the nations that forget God.
For*p the needy shall not alway be forgotten: the expectation of the poor shall not perish for ever.
Arise,*p O Lord;*s let not man prevail: let the heathen be judged in thy sight.
Put*p them in fear, O Lord:*s that the nations may know themselves to be but men. Selah.
